like someone strange.

214
00:15:23,689 --> 00:15:25,658
I'm a stand-in,
that's my game.

215
00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:26,959
I'm not in it for the fame.

216
00:15:27,059 --> 00:15:28,694
Don't call me no glamourpuss.

217
00:15:28,794 --> 00:15:30,496
I'm a stand-in, marvelous.

218
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:31,630
War in Europe.

219
00:15:31,730 --> 00:15:32,865
PEGGY: War in Spain.

220
00:15:32,965 --> 00:15:34,133
Newsreels.

221
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:35,668
They give me a pain.

222
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:37,169
Dust bowl, unemployment too.

223
00:15:37,269 --> 00:15:39,171
Honey, I got things to do.

224
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:40,939
PEGGY: Wardrobe
wants me in a gown.

225
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:43,609
Makeup thinks our
hair is too brown.

226
00:15:43,709 --> 00:15:45,344
I'm not in some unwashed mob.

227
00:15:45,444 --> 00:15:46,078
I'm a stand-in.

228
00:15:46,178 --> 00:15:47,179
That's my job.

229
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:48,347
PEGGY: I'm a stand-in.

230
00:15:48,447 --> 00:15:49,315
I'm true blue.

231
00:15:49,415 --> 00:15:51,550
My profession, [inaudible].

232
00:15:51,650 --> 00:15:52,651
I'm a stand-in.

233
00:15:52,751 --> 00:15:53,719
I got class.

234
00:15:53,819 --> 00:15:55,487
I'm a lady, bet your ass.

235
00:15:55,587 --> 00:15:56,455
I'm a stand-in.

236
00:15:56,555 --> 00:15:57,690
So is my pals.

237
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:59,825
We are not your average gals.

238
00:15:59,925 --> 00:16:05,064
We're together, thick and thin,
proud to be a genuine stand-in.

239
00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:09,735
Glad to see me, big boy?

240
00:16:09,835 --> 00:16:10,669
JACK: Mm-hm.

241
00:16:13,839 --> 00:16:15,341
That poem still kills me.

242
00:16:15,441 --> 00:16:16,742
PEGGY: God bless you, Jack.

243
00:16:16,842 --> 00:16:19,044
Me and Martha Anne knocked
out that little ditty

244
00:16:19,144 --> 00:16:22,915
over a couple of dozen Gin
Rickeys and some reefer.

245
00:16:23,015 --> 00:16:26,452
