01:18:15,257 --> 01:18:17,159
a couple of boys from homicide,
and the coroners, as fast

1304
01:18:17,259 --> 01:18:18,093
as you can.

1305
01:18:18,193 --> 01:18:20,128
Yeah.

1306
01:18:20,228 --> 01:18:22,064
Best reading I ever did,
and no one was filming it.

1307
01:18:24,633 --> 01:18:26,068
Oh, Martha Anne.

1308
01:18:26,168 --> 01:18:29,104
[crying] Ow.

1309
01:18:29,204 --> 01:18:30,906
Monica, you're
not going to die.

1310
01:18:31,006 --> 01:18:32,174
You just got a shot in the arm.

1311
01:18:32,274 --> 01:18:33,108
Ow.

1312
01:18:33,208 --> 01:18:33,809
[sirens]

1313
01:18:33,909 --> 01:18:35,343
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- Ow.

1314
01:18:35,444 --> 01:18:36,344
Ow.

1315
01:18:36,445 --> 01:18:37,345
OK, we're getting someone.

1316
01:18:37,446 --> 01:18:38,280
She's all right.

1317
01:18:38,380 --> 01:18:41,116
[tires squealing]

1318
01:18:41,216 --> 01:18:44,653
Yeah Ernie, I
know the lecture.

1319
01:18:44,753 --> 01:18:46,888
I know how life is.

1320
01:18:46,988 --> 01:18:49,591
Yeah, bad publicity.

1321
01:18:49,691 --> 01:18:50,726
I know.

1322
01:18:50,826 --> 01:18:53,228
I know murder is
bad for business.

1323
01:18:53,328 --> 01:18:56,298
I still say the Pagoda
should stay open.

1324
01:18:56,398 --> 01:18:58,667
No, I know how it works.

1325
01:18:58,767 --> 01:18:59,601
No, no, no, no.

1326
01:18:59,701 --> 01:19:00,936
You talk to him.

1327
01:19:01,036 --> 01:19:04,439
If he comes to his
senses, thank him for me.

1328
01:19:04,539 --> 01:19:07,576
Ernie, we owe it to ourselves.

1329
01:19:07,676 --> 01:19:08,477
OK.

1330
01:19:19,754 --> 01:19:20,822
Sure is dead around here.

1331
01:19:20,922 --> 01:19:22,090
MONICA: I know.

1332
01:19:22,190 --> 01:19:23,959
They suspended work
for one whole minute

1333
01:19:24,059 --> 01:19:25,460
in memory of Harlow.

1334
01:19:25,560 --> 01:19:28,096
11:00 to 11:01.

1335
01:19:28,196 --> 01:19:28,864
Mm.

1336
01:19:28,964 --> 01:19:30,432
So tell me what happened.

1337
01:19:30,532 --> 01:19:32,868
You should've seen
the look on Erwin's face

1338
01:19:32,968 --> 01:19:34,803
when I walked
through his office.

1339
01:19:34,903 --> 01:19:37,939
Erwin Reisner?

1340
01:19:38,039 --> 01:19:40,976
He didn't believe that
I had the balls to do it.

1341
01:19:41,076 --> 01:19:43,178
PEGGY: Neither did I.

1342
01:19:43,278 --> 01:19:47,682
So his secretary announced
me like I was royalty,

1343
01:19:47,782 --> 01:19:50,685
Eleanor Roosevelt to somebody.

1344
01:19:50,785 --> 01:19:54,189
And I looked him right
in the baby blues.

1345
01:19:54,289 --> 01:19:57,192
I could read his
smarmy little mind.

1346
01:19:57,292 --> 01:19:59,861
(LOW VOICE) What
does this bitch want?

1347
01:19:59,961 --> 01:20:04,432
But it came out, "Why
Monica, what a surprise."

1348
01:20:04,533 --> 01:20:08,103
So I said, "Don't get up, Erwin.

1349
01:20:08,203 --> 01:20:12,874
I just need a tiny
little favor."

1350
01:20:12,974 --> 01:20:15,744
So I put on my
best fuck me pout--

1351
01:20:15,844 --> 01:20:17,245
you know the one.

1352
01:20:17,345 --> 01:20:18,046
I do.

1353
01:20:18,146 --> 01:20:21,816
Martha Anne needs a lawyer.

1354
01:20:21,917 --> 01:20:24,719
And you know, Erwin runs
with all the big shots.

1355
01:20:24,820 --> 01:20:25,921
So he gives me a name.

1356
01:20:26,021 --> 01:20:27,756
PEGGY: You got
Martha Anne a lawyer?

1357
01:20:27,856 --> 01:20:28,657
[ringing]

1358
01:20:28,757 --> 01:20:29,958
Uh-huh.

1359
01:20:30,058 --> 01:20:31,726
Well, let me tell you
I spent my morning--

1360
01:20:31,826 --> 01:20:34,229
at the morgue.

1361
01:20:34,329 --> 01:20:36,965
Sweet Jesus, it's like
a Frigidaire down there.

1362
01:20:37,065 --> 01:20:41,169
And the morgue attendant
was wearing a fur coat.

1363
01:20:41,269 --> 01:20:47,809
And there she was, Taffy, laying
there like a smoked trout.

1364
01:20:47,909 --> 01:20:51,980
They asked me, "Is
this Taffy Entwistle?"

1365
01:20:52,080 --> 01:20:54,883
All I could do was just nod.

1366
01:20:54,983 --> 01:20:55,817
That's all it took.

1367
01:20:55,917 --> 01:20:57,819
She was identified.

1368
01:20:57,919 --> 01:21:00,055
And no Raymond Dubliet?

1369
01:21:00,155 --> 01:21:03,992
Not at the morgue, not at
the train depot, nowhere--

1370
01:21:04,092 --> 01:21:07,295
but he did send two guys
to pick up his Duesenberg.

1371
01:21:07,395 --> 01:21:11,600
Guys like that use girls
like us like tissue paper.

1372
01:21:11,700 --> 01:21:13,635
[whistle]

1373
01:21:13,735 --> 01:21:14,569
Jack!

1374
01:21:14,669 --> 01:21:15,570
Jack?

1375
01:21:15,670 --> 01:21:18,340
What are you doing here?

1376
01:21:18,440 --> 01:21:22,811
Job interview, [inaudible],,
assistant choreographer.

1377
01:21:22,911 --> 01:21:23,845
Did you get it?

1378
01:21:23,945 --> 01:21:25,013
Ah, this is showbiz, Peg.

1379
01:21:25,113 --> 01:21:26,381
I'll believe it
when I'm on the set.

1380
01:21:26,481 --> 01:21:29,050
Oh, ah.

1381
01:21:29,150 --> 01:21:32,320
Well, I spent the
morning at the morgue.

1382
01:21:32,420 --> 01:21:33,922
Oh, I found this.

1383
01:21:34,022 --> 01:21:35,657
I found this in Taffy's pocket.

1384
01:21:43,798 --> 01:21:46,901
"Variety, September 20, 1932--

1385
01:21:47,002 --> 01:21:50,805
the [inaudible] actress
Peg Entwistle, suicide.

1386
01:21:50,905 --> 01:21:54,142
Peg Entwistle, legitimate
actress who had slight picture

1387
01:21:54,242 --> 01:21:57,579
experience, was found dead in
the hills back of Hollywood

1388
01:21:57,679 --> 01:21:59,581
this morning by a pedestrian.

1389
01:21:59,681 --> 01:22:02,984
According to the police, she
had evidently jumped off the H

1390
01:22:03,084 --> 01:22:04,719
on the Hollywood sign.

1391
01:22:04,819 --> 01:22:07,088
With her was found this note--

1392
01:22:07,188 --> 01:22:11,159
afraid I am a coward, and
I'm worried for many things.

1393
01:22:11,259 --> 01:22:13,962
If only I would have
done this long ago,

1394
01:22:14,062 --> 01:22:16,431
I could've saved a lot of pain."

1395
01:22:16,531 --> 01:22:17,799
Taffy's sister.

1396
01:22:17,899 --> 01:22:20,402
Exactly.

1397
01:22:20,502 --> 01:22:21,803
[sigh]

1398
01:22:21,903 --> 01:22:23,505
What do you want to do?

1399
01:22:23,605 --> 01:22:24,439
Martini.

1400
01:22:24,539 --> 01:22:25,740
Let's get a drink!

1401
01:22:25,840 --> 01:22:27,742
Leave it to me.

1402
01:22:27,842 --> 01:22:30,278
To Taffy and Harlow.

1403
01:22:30,378 --> 01:22:33,448
May god welcome them to
the kingdom of heaven,

1404
01:22:33,548 --> 01:22:37,052
for eternal bliss,
salvation, and joy.

1405
01:22:41,589 --> 01:22:43,024
Hey, Rhonda.

1406
01:22:43,124 --> 01:22:46,194
Hey, Peg.

1407
01:22:46,294 --> 01:22:47,595
How's Deitrich, Rhonda?

1408
01:22:51,032 --> 01:22:52,033
Taffy.

1409
01:22:55,203 --> 01:22:57,839
God, I really loved her.

1410
01:22:57,939 --> 01:23:01,009
If only I could have been
here, I could have saved her.

1411
01:23:01,109 --> 01:23:02,210
You'd be dead.

1412
01:23:02,310 --> 01:23:04,679
Yeah, but you
ever meet someone,

1413
01:23:04,779 --> 01:23:07,248
and you just love them?

1414
01:23:07,349 --> 01:23:09,017
And maybe you have a
relationship, maybe

1415
01:23:09,117 --> 01:23:12,153
you don't-- it doesn't matter.

1416
01:23:12,253 --> 01:23:17,125
You love them anyway, and
you love them forever.

1417
01:23:17,225 --> 01:23:18,326
You hardly knew her.

1418
01:23:18,426 --> 01:23:19,661
[cat call]

1419
01:23:19,761 --> 01:23:22,130
JACK: Mm, wow.

1420
01:23:25,834 --> 01:23:27,068
Make it a Coke, Jack.

1421
01:23:32,374 --> 01:23:35,043
PEGGY: She's being
a good girl tonight.

1422
01:23:35,143 --> 01:23:36,945
SHIRLEY: Well, I'm
doing it for my health.

1423
01:23:37,045 --> 01:23:38,546
RHONDA: Health?

1424
01:23:38,646 --> 01:23:43,518
Shirl, your liver
expired with a repeal.

1425
01:23:43,618 --> 01:23:47,956
And that lovely set of matched
hypodermics in your purse?

1426
01:23:48,056 --> 01:23:49,824
Gone.

1427
01:23:49,924 --> 01:23:50,759
That easy?

1428
01:23:53,428 --> 01:23:54,262
Hell.

1429
01:23:57,098 --> 01:23:59,634
See, first you take
a vial of morphine,

1430
01:23:59,734 --> 01:24:03,071
and then you take a
vial of distilled water,

1431
01:24:03,171 --> 01:24:06,508
and for every amount of
morphine that you take out,

1432
01:24:06,608 --> 01:24:13,815
you replace it with water,
and soon it's all over.

1433
01:24:13,915 --> 01:24:17,385
Well, I mean, except for
the retching your guts out

1434
01:24:17,485 --> 01:24:22,457
and the not sleeping
for 72 hours.

1435
01:24:22,557 --> 01:24:24,125
But I think--

1436
01:24:24,225 --> 01:24:27,295
I think more clearly now.

1437
01:24:27,395 --> 01:24:29,631
And I see better, too.

1438
01:24:29,731 --> 01:24:30,532
And what do you see?

1439
01:24:35,003 --> 01:24:36,638
The future, Jack.

1440
01:24:39,274 --> 01:24:41,843
Let's get out of here.

1441
01:24:41,943 --> 01:24:44,546
You owe it to yourself.

1442
01:24:44,646 --> 01:24:45,847
PEGGY: Yeah, Jack.

1443
01:24:45,947 --> 01:24:46,915
Come on.

1444
01:24:47,015 --> 01:24:49,084
You're gonna get that job.

1445
01:24:49,184 --> 01:24:50,218
Come on, Jack.

1446
01:24:52,854 --> 01:24:54,456
Well, I'm a stand-in.

1447
01:24:54,556 --> 01:24:55,523
I'm OK.

1448
01:24:55,623 --> 01:24:58,793
16.50 every day.

1449
01:24:58,893 --> 01:25:02,097
Other girls are on the streets.

1450
01:25:02,197 --> 01:25:03,498
I'm a stand-in.

1451
01:25:03,598 --> 01:25:05,333
Life is sweet.

1452
01:25:05,433 --> 01:25:11,239
Paramount or MGM, Warner
Brothers-- all of them.

1453
01:25:11,339 --> 01:25:14,576
Come on, Jack!

1454
01:25:14,676 --> 01:25:16,978
I'm coming.

1455
01:25:17,078 --> 01:25:18,746
By, Ernie's!

1456
01:25:18,847 --> 01:25:21,716
They never did have
good Chinese food, anyway.

1457
01:25:21,816 --> 01:25:25,720
[music playing]

1458
01:26:42,997 --> 01:26:47,936
(SINGING) I want to be
happy, but I won't be happy

1459
01:26:48,036 --> 01:26:52,473
till I make you happy too.

1460
01:26:52,574 --> 01:26:57,111
Life's really wroth living
when we are mirth-giving.

1461
01:26:57,212 --> 01:27:01,449
Why can't I give some to you?

1462
01:27:01,549 --> 01:27:06,454
When skies are gray, and
you say you are blue,

1463
01:27:06,554 --> 01:27:11,192
I'll send a sun smiling through.

1464
01:27:11,292 --> 01:27:16,030
I want to be happy,
but I won't be happy

1465
01:27:16,130 --> 01:27:19,634
till I make you happy too.

